summary: Midnight Express: Directed by Alan Parker. With Brad Davis, Irene Miracle, Bo Hopkins, Paolo Bonacelli. Billy Hayes, an American college student, is caught smuggling drugs out of Turkey and thrown into prison.

title: Misery (1990)
summary: Misery: Directed by Rob Reiner. With James Caan, Kathy Bates, Richard Farnsworth, Frances Sternhagen. After a famous author is rescued from a car crash by a fan of his novels, he comes to realize that the care he is receiving is only the beginning of a nightmare of captivity and abuse.

title: Mr. Saturday Night (1992)
summary: Mr. Saturday Night: Directed by Billy Crystal. With Billy Crystal, David Paymer, Julie Warner, Helen Hunt. The life of Buddy Young, a comic legend in flashbacks but an old man looking for work in the present.

title: Murphy's Romance (1985)
summary: Murphy's Romance: Directed by Martin Ritt. With Sally Field, James Garner, Brian Kerwin, Corey Haim. Emma moves to a ranch with her son after a divorce and befriends the older Murphy, but things turn complicated when her ex shows up.

title: My Life (1993)
summary: My Life: Directed by Bruce Joel Rubin. With Michael Keaton, Nicole Kidman, Bradley Whitford, Queen Latifah. A terminally ill man prepares for his death.

title: Solaris (Solyaris) (1972)
summary: Solaris: Directed by Andrei Tarkovsky. With Natalya Bondarchuk, Donatas Banionis, Jüri Järvet, Vladislav Dvorzhetskiy. A psychologist is sent to a station orbiting a distant planet in order to discover what has caused the crew to go insane.

title: Network (1976)
summary: Network: Directed by Sidney Lumet. With Faye Dunaway, William Holden, Peter Finch, Robert Duvall. A television network cynically exploits a deranged former anchor's ravings and revelations about the news media for its own profit, but finds that his message may be difficult to control.

title: No Way Out (1987)
summary: No Way Out: Directed by Roger Donaldson. With Kevin Costner, Gene Hackman, Sean Young, Will Patton. A coverup and witchhunt occur after a politician accidentally kills his mistress.

title: North Dallas Forty (1979)
summary: North Dallas Forty: Directed by Ted Kotcheff. With Nick Nolte, Mac Davis, Charles Durning, Dayle Haddon. A satire of American professional football in which a veteran pass-catcher's individuality and refusal to become part of the team family are bitterly resented by his disciplinarian coaches.

title: Odd Couple, The (1968)
summary: The Odd Couple: Directed by Gene Saks. With Jack Lemmon, Walter Matthau, John Fiedler, Herb Edelman. A New Yorker newly separated from his wife moves in with his best friend, a divorced sportswriter, but their ideas of housekeeping and lifestyles are as different as night and day.

title: Outlaw Josey Wales, The (1976)
summary: The Outlaw Josey Wales: Directed by Clint Eastwood. With Clint Eastwood, Chief Dan George, Sondra Locke, Bill McKinney. Missouri farmer Josey Wales joins a Confederate guerrilla unit and winds up on the run from the Union soldiers who murdered his family.

title: Frequency (2000)
summary: Frequency: Directed by Gregory Hoblit. With Dennis Quaid, Jim Caviezel, Shawn Doyle, Elizabeth Mitchell. An accidental cross-time radio link connects father and son across 30 years. The son tries to save his father's life, but then must fix the consequences.

title: Ready to Rumble (2000)
summary: Ready to Rumble: Directed by Brian Robbins. With David Arquette, Oliver Platt, Scott Caan, Bill Goldberg. Two slacker wrestling fans are devastated by the ousting of their favorite character by an unscrupulous promoter.

title: Return to Me (2000)
summary: Return to Me: Directed by Bonnie Hunt. With David Duchovny, Minnie Driver, Carroll O'Connor, Robert Loggia. A man who falls in love with the woman who received his wife's heart must decide which woman it is who holds his heart.

title: Rules of Engagement (2000)
summary: Rules of Engagement: Directed by William Friedkin. With Tommy Lee Jones, Samuel L. Jackson, Guy Pearce, Ben Kingsley. An attorney defends an officer on trial for ordering his troops to fire on civilians after they stormed a U.S. embassy in a Middle Eastern country.
cast: Tommy Lee Jones|Samuel L. Jackson|Guy Pearce
stars: Tommy Lee Jones|Samuel L. Jackson|Guy Pearce

title: Joe Gould's Secret (2000)
summary: Joe Gould's Secret: Directed by Stanley Tucci. With Ian Holm, Stanley Tucci, Hope Davis, Sarah Hyland. Around 1940, The New Yorker staff writer Joe Mitchell meets Joe Gould, a Greenwich Village character, who is writing a voluminous Oral History of the World, a record of twenty thousand conversations he's overheard.

title: Me Myself I (2000)
summary: Me Myself I: Directed by Pip Karmel. With Rachel Griffiths, David Roberts, Sandy Winton, Yael Stone. Pamela Drury is unhappy and alone. On her birthday she stumbles across a photo of Robert Dickson and wonders what would've happened had she said yes to his proposal. A freak accident causes Pamela to live out the life she could've had, but is the grass on the other side always greener?

title: Bell, Book and Candle (1958)
summary: Een huis vol heksen: Directed by Richard Quine. With James Stewart, Kim Novak, Jack Lemmon, Ernie Kovacs. A modern-day witch likes her neighbor but despises his fiancée, so she enchants him to love her instead.

title: Force 10 from Navarone (1978)
summary: Force 10 from Navarone: Directed by Guy Hamilton. With Robert Shaw, Harrison Ford, Barbara Bach, Edward Fox. During World War II, several oddly assorted military experts are teamed in a mission to raid and destroy a bridge vital to enemy strategy.

title: Mystery Train (1989)
summary: Mystery Train: Directed by Jim Jarmusch. With Masatoshi Nagase, Yûki Kudô, Screamin' Jay Hawkins, Cinqué Lee. Three stories are connected by a Memphis hotel and the spirit of Elvis Presley.

title: Arthur (1981)
summary: Arthur: Directed by Steve Gordon. With Dudley Moore, Liza Minnelli, John Gielgud, Geraldine Fitzgerald. Alcoholic billionaire playboy Arthur Bach must marry a woman he does not love, or he will be cut off from his $750,000,000 fortune. But when Arthur falls in love with a poor waitress, he must decide if he wants to choose love or money.

title: Bachelor Party (1984)
summary: Bachelor Party: Directed by Neal Israel. With Tom Hanks, Tawny Kitaen, Adrian Zmed, George Grizzard. A soon-to-be-married man's friends throw him the ultimate bachelor party.

title: Parenthood (1989)
summary: Parenthood: Directed by Ron Howard. With Steve Martin, Mary Steenburgen, Dianne Wiest, Jason Robards. Three Buckman siblings attempt to raise their children - each in their own different style - and deal with the joys and sorrows that the process brings.

title: Predator (1987)
summary: Predator: Directed by John McTiernan. With Arnold Schwarzenegger, Carl Weathers, Elpidia Carrillo, Bill Duke. A team of commandos on a mission in a Central American jungle find themselves hunted by an extraterrestrial warrior.

title: Prince of Tides, The (1991)
summary: The Prince of Tides: Directed by Barbra Streisand. With Nick Nolte, Barbra Streisand, Blythe Danner, Kate Nelligan. A troubled man talks to his suicidal sister's psychiatrist about their family history and falls in love with her in the process.

title: Postman Always Rings Twice, The (1981)
summary: The Postman Always Rings Twice: Directed by Bob Rafelson. With Jack Nicholson, Jessica Lange, John Colicos, Michael Lerner. The sensuous wife of a lunch wagon proprietor and a rootless drifter begin a sordidly steamy affair and conspire to murder her Greek husband.

title: All the Vermeers in New York (1990)
summary: All the Vermeers in New York: Directed by Jon Jost. With Emmanuelle Chaulet, Katie Garner, Grace Phillips, Laurel Lee Kiefer. Anna, a French actress, is approached by financial broker Mark in the Vermeer room of a New York gallery. However, romance does not ensue.

title: 28 Days (2000)
summary: 28 Days: Directed by Betty Thomas. With Sandra Bullock, Viggo Mortensen, Dominic West, Elizabeth Perkins. A big-city newspaper columnist is forced to enter a drug and alcohol rehab center after ruining her sister's wedding and crashing a stolen limousine.

title: American Psycho (2000)
summary: American Psycho: Directed by Mary Harron. With Christian Bale, Justin Theroux, Josh Lucas, Bill Sage. A wealthy New York City investment banking executive, Patrick Bateman, hides his alternate psychopathic ego from his co-workers and friends as he delves deeper into his violent, hedonistic fantasies.

title: Keeping the Faith (2000)
summary: Keeping the Faith: Directed by Edward Norton. With Ben Stiller, Edward Norton, Jenna Elfman, Anne Bancroft. Two friends, a priest and a rabbi, fall in love with the same woman they knew in their youth, but the religious position of both men denies them romance.

title: Where the Money Is (2000)
summary: Where the Money Is: Directed by Marek Kanievska. With Paul Newman, Linda Fiorentino, Dermot Mulroney, Susan Barnes. Old bank robber Henry, paralyzed from a stroke, is moved from a prison hospital to a retirement home, where Carol is a nurse. She doesn't believe he's paralyzed and sees him as a way out of her boring life.

title: East is East (1999)
summary: East Is East: Directed by Damien O'Donnell. With Om Puri, Linda Bassett, Jordan Routledge, Archie Panjabi. In early 1970s England, a Pakistani father finds the authority he has previously maintained challenged by his increasingly Anglicized children.

title: Filth and the Fury, The (2000)
summary: The Filth and the Fury: Directed by Julien Temple. With Paul Cook, Steve Jones, John Lydon, Glen Matlock. A film about the career of the notorious punk rock band, the Sex Pistols.

title: Diner (1982)
summary: Diner: Directed by Barry Levinson. With Steve Guttenberg, Daniel Stern, Mickey Rourke, Kevin Bacon. A group of college-age buddies struggle with their imminent passage into adulthood in 1959 Baltimore.

title: Shakes the Clown (1992)
summary: Shakes the Clown: Directed by Bobcat Goldthwait. With Bobcat Goldthwait, Julie Brown, Bruce Baum, Steve Bean. Shakes is good at his job as party clown - when he's sober and shows up. Five druggy clowns frame him for the murder of his boss.

title: Cabaret (1972)
summary: Cabaret: Directed by Bob Fosse. With Liza Minnelli, Michael York, Helmut Griem, Joel Grey. A female girlie club entertainer in Weimar Republic era Berlin romances two men while the Nazi Party rises to power around them.

title: What Ever Happened to Baby Jane? (1962)
summary: Wat is er toch van Baby Jane terechtgekomen?: Directed by Robert Aldrich. With Bette Davis, Joan Crawford, Victor Buono, Wesley Addy. A former child star torments her paraplegic sister in their decaying Hollywood mansion.

title: Auntie Mame (1958)
summary: Wat 'n Tante: Directed by Morton DaCosta. With Rosalind Russell, Forrest Tucker, Coral Browne, Fred Clark. An orphan goes to live with his free-spirited aunt. Conflict ensues when the executor of his father's estate objects to the aunt's lifestyle.

title: Guys and Dolls (1955)
summary: Guys and Dolls: Directed by Joseph L. Mankiewicz. With Marlon Brando, Jean Simmons, Frank Sinatra, Vivian Blaine. In New York, a gambler is challenged to take a cold female missionary to Havana, but they fall for each other, and the bet has a hidden motive to finance a crap game.

title: The Hunger (1983)
summary: The Hunger: Directed by Tony Scott. With Catherine Deneuve, David Bowie, Susan Sarandon, Cliff De Young. A love triangle develops between a beautiful yet dangerous vampire (Catherine Deneuve), her cellist companion (David Bowie), and a gerontologist (Susan Sarandon).

title: Marathon Man (1976)
summary: Marathon Man: Directed by John Schlesinger. With Dustin Hoffman, Laurence Olivier, Roy Scheider, William Devane. After the shocking murder of his older brother, a New York history student finds himself inexplicably hounded by shadowy government agents on the trail of a Nazi war criminal who is trying to retrieve smuggled diamonds.

title: Caddyshack (1980)
summary: Caddyshack: Directed by Harold Ramis. With Chevy Chase, Rodney Dangerfield, Ted Knight, Michael O'Keefe. An exclusive golf course has to deal with a brash new member and a destructive dancing gopher.

title: Gossip (2000)
summary: Gossip: Directed by Davis Guggenheim. With James Marsden, Lena Headey, Norman Reedus, Kate Hudson. Three college students base their class project around gossip and how fast it spreads, which soon spirals out of control.

title: Love and Basketball (2000)
summary: Love & Basketball: Directed by Gina Prince-Bythewood. With Glenndon Chatman, Jess Willard, Chris Warren, Kyla Pratt. Monica and Quincy love and play basketball together through many life challenges from childhood to adulthood.

title: U-571 (2000)
summary: U-571: Directed by Jonathan Mostow. With Matthew McConaughey, Bill Paxton, Harvey Keitel, Jon Bon Jovi. A German submarine is boarded by disguised American submariners trying to capture their Enigma cipher machine.

title: Virgin Suicides, The (1999)
summary: The Virgin Suicides: Directed by Sofia Coppola. With James Woods, Kathleen Turner, Kirsten Dunst, Josh Hartnett. A group of male friends become obsessed with five mysterious sisters who are sheltered by their strict, religious parents in suburban Detroit in the mid 1970s.

title: Jennifer 8 (1992)
summary: Jennifer Eight: Directed by Bruce Robinson. With Andy Garcia, Lance Henriksen, Uma Thurman, Graham Beckel. John Berlin, a former Los Angeles homicide detective, investigates a multiple murder case in San Diego. The only witness is a blind girl to whom he is immediately attracted.

title: Limelight (1952)
summary: Limelight: Directed by Charles Chaplin. With Charles Chaplin, Claire Bloom, Nigel Bruce, Buster Keaton. A fading comedian and a suicidally despondent ballet dancer must look to each other to find purpose and hope in their lives.

title: Crow: Salvation, The (2000)
summary: The Crow: Salvation: Directed by Bharat Nalluri. With Kirsten Dunst, William Atherton, Debbie Fan, Eric Mabius. Alex Corvis returns to the world of the living to solve the murder of a young woman that he was wrongly accused of.

title: Flintstones in Viva Rock Vegas, The (2000)
summary: The Flintstones in Viva Rock Vegas: Directed by Brian Levant. With Mark Addy, Stephen Baldwin, Kristen Johnston, Jane Krakowski. In this live-action prequel to The Flintstones (1994), the Flintstones and the Rubbles go on a trip to Rock Vegas, where Wilma Slaghoople is pursued by playboy Chip Rockefeller.

title: Where the Heart Is (2000)
summary: Where the Heart Is: Directed by Matt Williams. With Natalie Portman, Ashley Judd, Stockard Channing, Joan Cusack. A pregnant seventeen-year-old rebuilds her life after being abandoned by her boyfriend at a Walmart in Sequoyah, Oklahoma.

title: Big Kahuna, The (2000)
summary: The Big Kahuna: Directed by John Swanbeck. With Kevin Spacey, Danny DeVito, Peter Facinelli, Paul Dawson. Two veteran salesmen dissect a sales pitch to a particular client, through their young protégé.

title: Bossa Nova (2000)
summary: Bossa Nova: Directed by Bruno Barreto. With Amy Irving, Antônio Fagundes, Alexandre Borges, Débora Bloch. A separated attorney in Rio sees an English teaching American widow and tries to woo her.

title: Smiling Fish and Goat on Fire (1999)
summary: Goat on Fire and Smiling Fish: Directed by Kevin Jordan. With Derick Martini, Amy Hathaway, Steven Martini, Heather Moudy. Two brothers share a house in the Fairfax district of LA: Tony a feckless actor, Chris an accountant. Both have relationships on rocky ground. As these emotions swirl, Tony meets his letter carrier, a single-mom named Kathy who's come to LA from Wyoming with her daughter, a budding actress. Chris meets Anna, an Italian beauty working in the States, for a few months, wrangling animals on movie sets. Chris also befriends Clive, an aging, crusty man whose longing for his recently-deceased wife is a portrait of true love. Can Clive's example help Chris sort out his love life, and can Tony grow up enough to see the possibilities with Kathy and her daughter?

title: Idiots, The (Idioterne) (1998)
summary: The Idiots: Directed by Lars von Trier. With Bodil Jørgensen, Jens Albinus, Anne Louise Hassing, Troels Lyby. The group of people gather at the house in Copenhagen suburb to break all the limitations and to bring out the "inner idiot" in themselves.

title: Time Code (2000)
summary: Timecode: Directed by Mike Figgis. With Xander Berkeley, Golden Brooks, Saffron Burrows, Viveka Davis. Four frames of simultaneous action that alternately follow a smitten lesbian lover as she obsesses over her partner's dalliances and the tense goings-on of a Hollywood film production company.

title: Carnosaur (1993)
summary: Carnosaur: Directed by Adam Simon, Darren Patrick Moloney. With Diane Ladd, Raphael Sbarge, Jennifer Runyon, Harrison Page. A genetically manipulated and very hungry dinosaur escapes from a bioengineering company and wreaks havoc on the local desert town. A security guard and a girl environmentalist try to stop both it and the company's doomsday bioweapon.

title: Carnosaur 2 (1995)
summary: Carnosaur 2: Directed by Louis Morneau. With John Savage, Cliff De Young, Don Stroud, Rick Dean. A team of scientists go to a nuclear mining facility to investigate a possible meltdown and instead find a large amount of cloned dinosaurs.

title: Carnosaur 3: Primal Species (1996)
summary: Carnosaur 3: Primal Species: Directed by Jonathan Winfrey. With Scott Valentine, Janet Gunn, Rick Dean, Anthony Peck. International terrorists get a surprise when their cargo turns out to contain living dinosaurs. The army commando team now have to think fast, if they want to prevent the extinction of the human species, instead of the reptiles.

title: Hidden, The (1987)
summary: The Hidden: Directed by Jack Sholder. With Kyle MacLachlan, Michael Nouri, Claudia Christian, Clarence Felder. A cop and an FBI agent race for answers after law abiding people suddenly become violent criminals.

title: Two Moon Junction (1988)
summary: Two Moon Junction: Directed by Zalman King. With Sherilyn Fenn, Richard Tyson, Louise Fletcher, Burl Ives. A young Southern débutante temporarily abandons her posh lifestyle and upcoming, semi-arranged marriage to have a lustful and erotic fling with a rugged drifter who works at a local carnival.

title: Gladiator (2000)
summary: Gladiator: Directed by Ridley Scott. With Russell Crowe, Joaquin Phoenix, Connie Nielsen, Oliver Reed. A former Roman General sets out to exact vengeance against the corrupt emperor who murdered his family and sent him into slavery.

title: Up at the Villa (2000)
summary: Up at the Villa: Directed by Philip Haas. With Kristin Scott Thomas, Sean Penn, Anne Bancroft, James Fox. A widow finds choosing a new husband might not be her choice at all, as the actions of her various prospects confine her freedom.

title: Human Traffic (1999)
summary: Human Traffic: Directed by Justin Kerrigan. With John Simm, Lorraine Pilkington, Shaun Parkes, Nicola Reynolds. Five youngsters embrace the 90s clubbing scene on a drug-fuelled weekend of partying in Cardiff.

title: Breathless (1983)
summary: Breathless: Directed by Jim McBride. With Richard Gere, Valérie Kaprisky, Art Metrano, John P. Ryan. When Jesse Lujack steals a car in Las Vegas and drives down to LA, his criminal ways only escalate - but when will it end?

title: The Idolmaker (1980)
summary: The Idolmaker: Directed by Taylor Hackford. With Ray Sharkey, Tovah Feldshuh, Peter Gallagher, Paul Land. Based on the life of rock promoter/producer Bob Marcucci, who discovered, among others, Frankie Avalon and Fabian.

title: Inferno (1980)
summary: Inferno: Directed by Dario Argento. With Leigh McCloskey, Irene Miracle, Eleonora Giorgi, Daria Nicolodi. An American college student in Rome and his sister in New York investigate a series of killings in both locations where their resident addresses are the domain of two covens of witches.

title: Lords of Flatbush, The (1974)
summary: The Lords of Flatbush: Directed by Martin Davidson, Stephen Verona. With Perry King, Sylvester Stallone, Henry Winkler, Paul Mace. Two members of a social club in 1950s Brooklyn have more interest in romance than in rumbles.

title: Mr. Mom (1983)
summary: Mr. Mom: Directed by Stan Dragoti. With Michael Keaton, Teri Garr, Frederick Koehler, Taliesin Jaffe. After he's suddenly laid off, a husband switches roles with his wife. She returns to the workforce, and he becomes a stay-at-home dad, and he has to take care of three young children, a job he has no clue how to do.

title: Time Masters (Maîtres du temps, Les) (1982)
summary: Les maîtres du temps: Directed by René Laloux. With Jean Valmont, Michel Elias, Frédéric Legros, Yves-Marie Maurin. Piel, a 7 or 8 year old boy, is alone on the desert planet Perdide, only survivor of an attack by giant hornets. Calling for help, Piel's father's friend Jaffar keeps contact with the kid and hurries across space toward Perdide.

title: Battlefield Earth (2000)
summary: Battlefield Earth: Directed by Roger Christian. With John Travolta, Barry Pepper, Forest Whitaker, Kim Coates. It's the year 3000 A.D., and the Earth is lost to the alien race of Psychlos. Humanity is enslaved by these gold-thirsty tyrants, who are unaware that their 'man-animals' are about to ignite the rebellion of a lifetime.

title: Center Stage (2000)
summary: Center Stage: Directed by Nicholas Hytner. With Amanda Schull, Christine Dunham, Stephen Stout, Maryann Plunkett. A group of 12 teenagers from various backgrounds enroll at the American Ballet Academy in New York to make it as ballet dancers and each one deals with the problems and stress of training and getting ahead in the world of dance.

title: Screwed (2000)
summary: Screwed: Directed by Scott Alexander, Larry Karaszewski. With Norm MacDonald, Dave Chappelle, Elaine Stritch, Danny DeVito. A chauffeur kidnaps his rich boss's dog to hold it for ransom, but when she accidentally gets the dog back, she thinks that it's the chauffeur who's been kidnapped.

title: Whipped (2000)
summary: Whipped: Directed by Peter M. Cohen. With Amanda Peet, Brian Van Holt, Jonathan Abrahams, Zorie Barber. Three egotistical swingers, who think they're God's gift to women, end up having their friendships tested when all three of them pick up and start dating the same woman.

title: Hamlet (2000)
summary: Hamlet: Directed by Michael Almereyda. With Ethan Hawke, Kyle MacLachlan, Diane Venora, Sam Shepard. Modern-day New York City adaptation of Shakespeare's immortal story about Hamlet's plight to avenge his father's murder.

title: Anchors Aweigh (1945)
summary: Licht het anker: Directed by George Sidney, Joseph Barbera, William Hanna. With Frank Sinatra, Kathryn Grayson, Gene Kelly, José Iturbi. A pair of sailors on leave try to help a movie extra become a singing star.

title: Gypsy (1962)
summary: Gypsy: Directed by Mervyn LeRoy. With Rosalind Russell, Natalie Wood, Karl Malden, Paul Wallace. Based on the Broadway hit about the life and times of burlesque dancer Gypsy Rose Lee and her aggressive stage mother, Mama Rose.

title: On the Town (1949)
summary: Hallo... New York: Directed by Stanley Donen, Gene Kelly. With Gene Kelly, Frank Sinatra, Betty Garrett, Ann Miller. Three sailors wreak havoc as they search for love during a whirlwind 24-hour leave in New York City.

title: Pee-wee's Big Adventure (1985)
summary: Pee-wee's Big Adventure: Directed by Tim Burton. With Paul Reubens, Elizabeth Daily, Mark Holton, Diane Salinger. When eccentric man-child Pee-wee Herman gets his beloved bike stolen in broad daylight, he sets out across the U.S. on the adventure of his life.

title: Regret to Inform (1998)
summary: Regret to Inform: Directed by Barbara Sonneborn. With Xuan Ngoc Nguyen, Barbara Sonneborn. In this film made over ten years, filmmaker Barbara Sonneborn goes on a pilgrimage to the Vietnamese countryside where her husband was killed. She and translator (and fellow war widow) Xuan Ngoc Nguyen explore the meaning of war and loss on a human level. The film weaves interviews with Vietnamese and American widows into a vivid testament to the legacy of war.

title: Honeymoon in Vegas (1992)
summary: Honeymoon in Vegas: Directed by Andrew Bergman. With James Caan, Nicolas Cage, Sarah Jessica Parker, Pat Morita. Jack loses $65,000 in poker in Las Vegas, where he's marrying Betsy. The wedding will have to wait as the poker winner wants the weekend with Betsy to cancel the debt. She accepts. Whom will she marry?

title: Dinosaur (2000)
summary: Dinosaur: Directed by Eric Leighton, Ralph Zondag. With Alfre Woodard, Ossie Davis, Max Casella, Hayden Panettiere. An orphaned dinosaur raised by lemurs joins an arduous trek to a sanctuary after a meteorite shower destroys his family home.

title: Loser (2000)
summary: Loser: Directed by Amy Heckerling. With Jason Biggs, Mena Suvari, Zak Orth, Thomas Sadoski. A college student, branded a loser by his roommates and booted from the dorm, falls in love with a coed who has eyes for their condescending professor.

title: Road Trip (2000)
summary: Road Trip: Directed by Todd Phillips. With Breckin Meyer, Seann William Scott, Amy Smart, Paulo Costanzo. Four college buddies embark on a road trip to retrieve an illicit tape mistakenly mailed to a female friend.

title: Small Time Crooks (2000)
summary: Small Time Crooks: Directed by Woody Allen. With Woody Allen, Carolyn Saxon, Tracey Ullman, Michael Rapaport. A loser of a crook and his wife strike it rich when a botched bank job's cover business becomes a spectacular success.

title: Hollywood Knights, The (1980)
summary: The Hollywood Knights: Directed by Floyd Mutrux. With Julius Averitt, Steve Ballard, Phil Berle, Mike Binder. Led by their comedic leader, Turk, the Hollywood Knights car club raise hell throughout Beverly Hills on Halloween Night, 1965.

title: Twelve Chairs, The (1970)
summary: The Twelve Chairs: Directed by Mel Brooks. With Ron Moody, Frank Langella, Dom DeLuise, Andréas Voutsinas. In 1920s Soviet Russia, a fallen aristocrat, a priest and a con artist search for a treasure of jewels hidden inside one of twelve dining chairs, lost during the revolution.

title: Mission: Impossible II (2000)
summary: Mission: Impossible II: Directed by John Woo. With Tom Cruise, Dougray Scott, Thandiwe Newton, Ving Rhames. IMF agent Ethan Hunt is sent to Sydney to find and destroy a genetically modified disease called "Chimera".

title: Shanghai Noon (2000)
summary: Shanghai Noon: Directed by Tom Dey. With Jackie Chan, Owen Wilson, Lucy Liu, Brandon Merrill. A Chinese man travels to the Wild West to rescue a kidnapped Princess. After teaming up with a train robber, the unlikely duo takes on a Chinese traitor and his corrupt boss.

title: Better Living Through Circuitry (1999)
summary: Better Living Through Circuitry: Directed by Jon Reiss. With Moby, Lord T. Byron, McGuinnes, Lady Galore. This is a documentary film about the history of the U.S. rave scene which includes a fantastic soundtrack. Both the film and soundtrack capture the people and the music that shaped the underground subculture around electronic music in America. Featured soundtrack artists include: Moby, Keoki, The Crystal Method, DJ Spooky, Roni Size, Psychic TV, and a host of others.

title: 8 ½ Women (a.k.a. 8 1/2 Women) (a.k.a. Eight and a Half Women) (1999)
summary: 8 ½ Women: Directed by Peter Greenaway. With John Standing, Matthew Delamere, Vivian Wu, Annie Shizuka Inoh. Following the death of a mother, a father and son open up their very own harem in their Genevan estate after watching 8½ (1963).

title: Carnival of Souls (1962)
summary: Carnival of Souls: Directed by Herk Harvey. With Candace Hilligoss, Frances Feist, Sidney Berger, Art Ellison. After a traumatic accident, a woman becomes drawn to a mysterious abandoned carnival.

title: Flying Tigers (1942)
summary: De vliegende tijgers: Directed by David Miller. With John Wayne, John Carroll, Anna Lee, Paul Kelly. Capt. Jim Gordon's command of the famed American mercenary fighter group in China is complicated by the recruitment of an old friend who is a reckless hotshot.

title: Gold Rush, The (1925)
summary: The Gold Rush: Directed by Charles Chaplin. With Charles Chaplin, Mack Swain, Tom Murray, Henry Bergman. A prospector goes to the Klondike during the 1890s gold rush in hopes of making his fortune, and is smitten with a girl he sees in a dance hall.

title: Monsieur Verdoux (1947)
summary: Monsieur Verdoux: Directed by Charles Chaplin. With Charles Chaplin, Mady Correll, Allison Roddan, Robert Lewis. A suave but cynical man supports his family by marrying and murdering rich women for their money, but the job has some occupational hazards.

title: On Her Majesty's Secret Service (1969)
summary: On Her Majesty's Secret Service: Directed by Peter R. Hunt. With George Lazenby, Diana Rigg, Telly Savalas, Gabriele Ferzetti. James Bond woos a mob boss' daughter and goes undercover to uncover the true reason for Ernst Stavro Blofeld's allergy research in the Swiss Alps involving beautiful women from around the world.

title: Seven Days in May (1964)
summary: Seven Days in May: Directed by John Frankenheimer. With Burt Lancaster, Kirk Douglas, Fredric March, Ava Gardner. United States military leaders plot to overthrow the President because he supports a nuclear disarmament treaty and they fear a Soviet sneak attack.

title: Spy Who Loved Me, The (1977)
summary: The Spy Who Loved Me: Directed by Lewis Gilbert. With Roger Moore, Barbara Bach, Curd Jürgens, Richard Kiel. James Bond investigates the hijacking of British and Russian submarines carrying nuclear warheads, with the help of a K.G.B. agent whose lover he killed.

title: Vagabond (Sans toit ni loi) (1985)
summary: Sans toit ni loi: Directed by Agnès Varda. With Sandrine Bonnaire, Setti Ramdane, Francis Balchère, Jean-Louis Perletti. A young woman's body is found frozen in a ditch. Through flashbacks and interviews, we see the events that led to her inevitable death.

title: Moonraker (1979)

title: Blood In, Blood Out (1993)
summary: Blood In, Blood Out: Directed by Taylor Hackford. With Damian Chapa, Jesse Borrego, Benjamin Bratt, Enrique Castillo. Based on the true life experiences of poet Jimmy Santiago Baca, the film focuses on step-brothers Paco and Cruz, and their bi-racial cousin Miklo.

title: F/X (1986)
summary: F/X: Directed by Robert Mandel. With Bryan Brown, Brian Dennehy, Diane Venora, Cliff De Young. A movie special effects man is hired to fake a real-life mob killing for a witness protection plan, but finds his own life in danger.

title: F/X2 (a.k.a. F/X 2 - The Deadly Art of Illusion) (1991)
summary: F/X2: Directed by Richard Franklin. With Bryan Brown, Brian Dennehy, Rachel Ticotin, Joanna Gleason. A special effects man helps his girlfriend's ex, a cop, with a sting operation, where the ex gets killed. Something's off and he investigates with help from an ex-cop PI friend.

title: Hot Spot, The (1990)
summary: The Hot Spot: Directed by Dennis Hopper. With Don Johnson, Virginia Madsen, Jennifer Connelly, Charles Martin Smith. Upon arriving to a small town, a drifter quickly gets into trouble with the local authorities - and the local women - after he robs a bank.

title: Missing in Action (1984)
summary: Missing in Action: Directed by Joseph Zito. With Chuck Norris, M. Emmet Walsh, David Tress, Lenore Kasdorf. Colonel Braddock launches a mission deep into the jungles of Vietnam to find the POW camp that he escaped from and free the Americans still held captive there.

title: Missing in Action 2: The Beginning (1985)
summary: Missing in Action 2: The Beginning: Directed by Lance Hool. With Chuck Norris, Soon-Tek Oh, Steven Williams, Bennett Ohta. Prequel to the first Missing In Action, set in the early 1980s it shows the capture of Colonel Braddock during the Vietnam war in the 1970s, and his captivity with other American POWs in a brutal prison camp, and his plans to escape.

title: Braddock: Missing in Action III (1988)
summary: Braddock: Missing in Action III: Directed by Aaron Norris. With Chuck Norris, Aki Aleong, Roland Harrah III, Miki Kim. Braddock mounts a one-man assault to free his wife and son who are still being held in a Vietnam prison camp.

title: Thunderbolt and Lightfoot (1974)
summary: Thunderbolt and Lightfoot: Directed by Michael Cimino. With Clint Eastwood, Jeff Bridges, Geoffrey Lewis, Catherine Bach. With the help of an irreverent young sidekick, a bank robber gets his old gang back together to organize a daring new heist.

title: Dreamscape (1984)
summary: Dreamscape: Directed by Joseph Ruben. With Dennis Quaid, Max von Sydow, Christopher Plummer, Eddie Albert. A man who can enter and manipulate people's dreams is recruited by a government agency to help cure the President of the United States of his nightmares about nuclear war but stumbles upon an assassination plot.

title: The Golden Voyage of Sinbad (1973)
summary: The Golden Voyage of Sinbad: Directed by Gordon Hessler. With John Phillip Law, Caroline Munro, Tom Baker, Douglas Wilmer. Sinbad and the vizier of Marabia, followed by evil magician Koura, seek the three golden tablets that can gain them access to the ancient temple of the Oracle of All Knowledge.

title: House Party (1990)
summary: House Party: Directed by Reginald Hudlin. With Christopher Reid, Robin Harris, Christopher Martin, Martin Lawrence. Kid decides to go to his friend Play's house party, but neither of them can predict what's in store for them on what could be the wildest night of their lives.

title: House Party 2 (1991)
summary: House Party 2: Directed by George Jackson, Doug McHenry. With Christopher Reid, Christopher Martin, Martin Lawrence, Bowlegged Lou. When Kid's college money is stolen by a crooked music promoter, Play's solution is to stage the 'mutha' of all pajama parties. Starring Kid 'n Play and Martin Lawrence.

title: Croupier (1998)
summary: Croupier: Directed by Mike Hodges. With Clive Owen, Nick Reding, Nicholas Ball, Alexander Morton. An aspiring writer is hired as a croupier at a casino, where he realizes that his life as a croupier would make a great novel.

title: Kid, The (2000)
summary: The Kid: Directed by Jon Turteltaub. With Bruce Willis, Spencer Breslin, Emily Mortimer, Lily Tomlin. An unhappy and disliked image consultant gets a second shot at life when he is mysteriously confronted by an eight-year-old version of himself.

title: Scary Movie (2000)
summary: Scary Movie: Directed by Keenen Ivory Wayans. With Carmen Electra, Dave Sheridan, Frank B. Moore, Giacomo Baessato. A year after disposing of the body of a man they accidentally killed, a group of dumb teenagers are stalked by a bumbling serial killer.

title: But I'm a Cheerleader (1999)
summary: But I'm a Cheerleader: Directed by Jamie Babbit. With Natasha Lyonne, Michelle Williams, Brandt Wille, Bud Cort. A naive teenager is sent to rehab camp when her straitlaced parents and friends suspect her of being a lesbian.

title: Shower (Xizao) (1999)
summary: Xi zao: Directed by Yang Zhang. With Jiayi Du, Zheng Fang, Bing He, Wu Jiang. A young wealthy businessman's icy attitude toward his working-class background is about to thaw as he is forced to reconnect with his elderly father and mentally challenged younger brother, who together run a public bathhouse.

title: Blow-Up (Blowup) (1966)
summary: Blow-Up: Directed by Michelangelo Antonioni. With Vanessa Redgrave, Sarah Miles, David Hemmings, John Castle. A fashion photographer unknowingly captures a death on film after following two lovers in a park.

title: Pawnbroker, The (1964)
summary: The Pawnbroker: Directed by Sidney Lumet. With Rod Steiger, Geraldine Fitzgerald, Brock Peters, Jaime Sánchez. A Jewish pawnbroker, victim of Nazi persecution, loses all faith in his fellow man until he realizes too late the tragedy of his actions.

title: Groove (2000)
summary: Groove: Directed by Greg Harrison. With Chris Ferreira, Mackenzie Firgens, Elizabeth Sun, Steve Van Wormer. An inside look into one night in the San Francisco underground rave scene.

title: Footloose (1984)
summary: Footloose: Directed by Herbert Ross. With Kevin Bacon, Lori Singer, John Lithgow, Dianne Wiest. A city teenager moves to a small town where rock music and dancing have been banned, and his rebellious spirit shakes up the populace.

title: Duel in the Sun (1946)
summary: Duel in de zon: Directed by King Vidor, Otto Brower, William Dieterle, Sidney Franklin, William Cameron Menzies, David O. Selznick, Josef von Sternberg. With Jennifer Jones, Joseph Cotten, Gregory Peck, Lionel Barrymore. Beautiful, biracial Pearl Chavez becomes the ward of her dead father's first love and finds herself torn between two brothers, one good and the other bad.

title: X-Men (2000)
summary: X-Men: Directed by Bryan Singer. With Hugh Jackman, Patrick Stewart, Ian McKellen, Famke Janssen. In a world where mutants (evolved super-powered humans) exist and are discriminated against, two groups form for an inevitable clash: the supremacist Brotherhood, and the pacifist X-Men.

title: Chuck & Buck (2000)
summary: Chuck & Buck: Directed by Miguel Arteta. With Mike White, Chris Weitz, Lupe Ontiveros, Beth Colt. An oddly naive man-child stalks his childhood best friend and tries to reconnect with their past.

title: Five Senses, The (1999)
summary: The Five Senses: Directed by Jeremy Podeswa. With Molly Parker, Gabrielle Rose, Elize Frances Stolk, Nadia Litz. Interconnected stories examine situations involving the five senses. Touch is represented by a massage therapist who is treating a woman, while her daughter accidentally loses the woman's pre-school daughter in the park. The older daughter meets a voyeur (vision), a professional house-cleaner has an acute sense of smell, a cake maker has lost her sense of taste, and an older man is losing his hearing.

title: In Crowd, The (2000)
summary: The In Crowd: Directed by Mary Lambert. With Susan Ward, Lori Heuring, Matthew Settle, Nathan Bexton. A mentally disturbed young woman takes a job at a posh country club and falls in with a clique of wealthy college kids where she's taken under the wing of the clique's twisted leader, who harbors some dark secrets too terrifying to tell.

title: What Lies Beneath (2000)
summary: What Lies Beneath: Directed by Robert Zemeckis. With Michelle Pfeiffer, Katharine Towne, Miranda Otto, James Remar. The wife of a university research scientist believes that her lakeside Vermont home is haunted by a ghost - or that she is losing her mind.

title: Pokémon the Movie 2000 (2000)
summary: Pokémon 2: De Film - Op Eigen Kracht: Directed by Kunihiko Yuyama, Michael Haigney. With Rica Matsumoto, Ikue Ôtani, Unshô Ishizuka, Mayumi Izuka. Ash Ketchum must gather the three spheres of fire, ice and lightning in order to restore balance to the Orange Islands.

title: Anatomy of a Murder (1959)
summary: Anatomy of a Murder: Directed by Otto Preminger. With James Stewart, Lee Remick, Ben Gazzara, Arthur O'Connell. An upstate Michigan lawyer defends a soldier who claims he killed an innkeeper due to temporary insanity after the victim raped his wife. What is the truth, and will he win his case?

title: Freejack (1992)
summary: Freejack: Directed by Geoff Murphy. With Emilio Estevez, Mick Jagger, Rene Russo, Anthony Hopkins. Bounty hunters from the future transport a doomed race car driver to New York City in 2009, where his mind will be replaced with that of a dead billionaire.

title: Mackenna's Gold (1969)
summary: Mackenna's Gold: Directed by J. Lee Thompson. With Gregory Peck, Omar Sharif, Telly Savalas, Camilla Sparv. A bandit kidnaps a Marshal who has seen a map showing a gold vein on Indian lands, but other groups are looking for it too, while the Apache try to keep the secret location undisturbed.

title: Sinbad and the Eye of the Tiger (1977)
summary: Sinbad en het oog van de tijger: Directed by Sam Wanamaker. With Patrick Wayne, Taryn Power, Margaret Whiting, Jane Seymour. Sinbad The Sailor sails to deliver a cursed prince to a dangerous island in the face of deadly opposition from a powerful witch.

title: Two Women (Ciociara, La) (1960)
summary: La ciociara: Directed by Vittorio De Sica. With Sophia Loren, Jean-Paul Belmondo, Eleonora Brown, Carlo Ninchi. In the Italy of WWII, a widow and her lonely daughter seek for distance between them and the horrors of war.

title: What About Bob? (1991)
summary: What About Bob?: Directed by Frank Oz. With Bill Murray, Richard Dreyfuss, Julie Hagerty, Charlie Korsmo. A successful psychotherapist loses his mind after one of his most dependent patients, an obsessive-compulsive neurotic, tracks him down during his family vacation.

title: White Sands (1992)
summary: White Sands: Directed by Roger Donaldson. With Willem Dafoe, Mary Elizabeth Mastrantonio, Mickey Rourke, Samuel L. Jackson. A small southwestern town Sheriff finds a body in the desert with a suitcase and five hundred thousand dollars. He impersonates the man and stumbles into an F.B.I. investigation.

title: Breaker Morant (1980)
summary: 'Breaker' Morant: Directed by Bruce Beresford. With Edward Woodward, Jack Thompson, John Waters, Bryan Brown. Three Australian lieutenants are court martialed for executing prisoners as a way of deflecting attention from war crimes committed by their superior officers.

title: Everything You Always Wanted to Know About Sex * But Were Afraid to Ask (1972)
summary: Everything You Always Wanted to Know About Sex * But Were Afraid to Ask: Directed by Woody Allen. With Woody Allen, John Carradine, Lou Jacobi, Louise Lasser. Seven stories are trying to answer the question: what is sex? Or maybe they are not trying.

title: Interiors (1978)
summary: Interiors: Directed by Woody Allen. With Kristin Griffith, Mary Beth Hurt, Richard Jordan, Diane Keaton. Three sisters find their lives spinning out of control in the wake of their parents' sudden, unexpected divorce.

title: Love and Death (1975)
summary: Love and Death: Directed by Woody Allen. With Woody Allen, Diane Keaton, Georges Adet, Frank Adu. In czarist Russia, a neurotic soldier and his distant cousin formulate a plot to assassinate Napoleon.

title: Official Story, The (La historia oficial) (1985)
summary: La historia oficial: Directed by Luis Puenzo. With Héctor Alterio, Norma Aleandro, Chunchuna Villafañe, Hugo Arana. During the final months of Argentinian Military Dictatorship in 1983, a high school teacher sets out to find out who the mother of her adopted daughter is.

title: Tampopo (1985)
summary: Tampopo: Directed by Jûzô Itami. With Tsutomu Yamazaki, Nobuko Miyamoto, Kôji Yakusho, Ken Watanabe. A truck driver stops at a small family-run noodle shop and decides to help its fledgling business. The story is intertwined with various vignettes about the relationship of love and food.

title: Nutty Professor II: The Klumps (2000)
summary: Nutty Professor II: The Klumps: Directed by Peter Segal. With Eddie Murphy, Janet Jackson, Larry Miller, John Ales. Scientist Sherman Klump's inventions, his upcoming marriage to his pretty colleague Denise Gaines, and his reputation, are threatened by his evil clone Buddy Love.

title: Girl on the Bridge, The (Fille sur le pont, La) (1999)
summary: La fille sur le pont: Directed by Patrice Leconte. With Vanessa Paradis, Daniel Auteuil, Frédéric Pfluger, Dimitris Georgalas. One night, a fading entertainer intervenes when a woman contemplates suicide, beginning a strange, unpredictable relationship.

title: Wonderland (1999)
summary: Wonderland: Directed by Michael Winterbottom. With Shirley Henderson, Gina McKee, Molly Parker, Ian Hart. There's little wonder in the working-class lives of Bill, Eileen, and their three grown daughters. They're lonely Londoners. Nadia, a café waitress, places personal ads, looking for love; Debbie, a single mother, entertains men at the hair salon after hours; her son spends part of the weekend with her ex, a man with a hair-trigger temper. Molly is expecting her first baby and the child's father acts as if the responsibility is too much for him. Eileen is bitter, complaining about her husband and the dog next door; Bill's a doormat. His West Indian neighbour offers him a drink; her own grown son locks himself in his room most of the time. Will anyone connect during this Guy Fawkes weekend?

title: Autumn in New York (2000)
summary: Autumn in New York: Directed by Joan Chen. With Richard Gere, Winona Ryder, Anthony LaPaglia, Elaine Stritch. Romantic drama about an aging playboy who falls for a sweet, but terminally ill, young woman.

title: Coyote Ugly (2000)
summary: Coyote Ugly: Directed by David McNally. With Piper Perabo, Adam Garcia, John Goodman, Maria Bello. Aspiring songwriter Violet Sanford, after getting a job at a women-run NYC bar that teases its male patrons, comes out of her shell.

title: Hollow Man (2000)
summary: Hollow Man: Directed by Paul Verhoeven. With Elisabeth Shue, Kevin Bacon, Josh Brolin, Kim Dickens. A brilliant scientist's discovery renders him invisible, but transforms him into an omnipotent, dangerous megalomaniac.

title: Space Cowboys (2000)
summary: Space Cowboys: Directed by Clint Eastwood. With Clint Eastwood, Tommy Lee Jones, Donald Sutherland, James Garner. When retired engineer Frank Corvin (Clint Eastwood) is called upon to rescue a failing satellite, he insists that his equally old teammates accompany him into space.

title: Psycho Beach Party (2000)
summary: Psycho Beach Party: Directed by Robert Lee King. With Lauren Ambrose, Thomas Gibson, Nicholas Brendon, Kimberley Davies. Chicklet is a sixteen-year old tomboy who's desperate to be part of the in-crowd of Malibu beach surfers. She's the typical American girl - except for one little problem: her personality is split into more slices than a pepperoni pizza.

title: Saving Grace (2000)
summary: Saving Grace: Directed by Nigel Cole. With Brenda Blethyn, Craig Ferguson, Martin Clunes, Tchéky Karyo. A small-town English widow, facing financial troubles after her husband's suicide, turns to agriculture of an illegal kind.

title: Black Sabbath (Tre volti della paura, I) (1963)
summary: Drie aangezichten van de verschrikking: Directed by Mario Bava. With Michèle Mercier, Lidia Alfonsi, Boris Karloff, Mark Damon. Boris Karloff hosts a trio of horror stories concerning a stalked call girl, a vampire-like monster who preys on his family, and a nurse who is haunted by her ring's rightful owner.

title: Brain That Wouldn't Die, The (1962)
summary: The Brain That Wouldn't Die: Directed by Joseph Green. With Jason Evers, Virginia Leith, Anthony La Penna, Adele Lamont. A doctor experimenting with transplant techniques keeps his girlfriend's head alive when she is decapitated in a car crash, then goes hunting for a new body.

title: Bronco Billy (1980)
summary: Bronco Billy: Directed by Clint Eastwood. With Clint Eastwood, Sondra Locke, Geoffrey Lewis, Scatman Crothers. An idealistic, modern-day cowboy struggles to keep his Wild West show afloat in the face of hard luck and waning interest.

title: Crush, The (1993)
summary: The Crush: Directed by Alan Shapiro. With Cary Elwes, Alicia Silverstone, Jennifer Rubin, Kurtwood Smith. A journalist becomes the unwanted center of attention for a 14-year-old girl, who proceeds to sabotage his life after he refuses her sexual advances.

title: Kelly's Heroes (1970)
summary: Kelly's Heroes: Directed by Brian G. Hutton. With Clint Eastwood, Telly Savalas, Don Rickles, Carroll O'Connor. A group of U.S. soldiers sneaks across enemy lines to get their hands on a secret stash of Nazi treasure.

title: Phantasm II (1988)
summary: Phantasm II: Directed by Don Coscarelli. With James Le Gros, Reggie Bannister, Angus Scrimm, Paula Irvine. Mike, now released from a psychiatric hospital, meets with Reggie, and discover his dreams ( the events of the original film) are real, and they both journey to find and stop the evil Tall Man from his grim work.

title: Phantasm III: Lord of the Dead (1994)
summary: Phantasm III: Lord of the Dead: Directed by Don Coscarelli. With Reggie Bannister, A. Michael Baldwin, Bill Thornbury, Gloria Lynne Henry. Mike and Reggie continue to hunt the mysterious Tall Man, discovering along the way that the invasion has already begun.

title: Phantasm IV: Oblivion (1998)
summary: Phantasm IV: Oblivion: Directed by Don Coscarelli. With A. Michael Baldwin, Reggie Bannister, Bill Thornbury, Heidi Marnhout. Mike travels through time and dimensions to find the Tall Man's origins.

title: Pumpkinhead (1988)
summary: Pumpkinhead: Directed by Stan Winston. With Lance Henriksen, Jeff East, John D'Aquino, Kimberly Ross. After a tragic accident, a man conjures up a towering, vengeful demon called Pumpkinhead to destroy a group of unsuspecting teenagers.

title: Air America (1990)
summary: Air America: Directed by Roger Spottiswoode. With Mel Gibson, Robert Downey Jr., Nancy Travis, Ken Jenkins. A young pilot finds himself recruited unwittingly into a covert and corrupt CIA airlift operation in Laos during the Vietnam conflict.

title: Sleepaway Camp (1983)
summary: Sleepaway Camp: Directed by Robert Hiltzik. With Felissa Rose, Jonathan Tiersten, Karen Fields, Christopher Collet. Angela Baker, a shy, traumatized young girl, is sent to summer camp with her cousin. Shortly after her arrival, anyone with sinister or less than honorable intentions toward her gets their comeuppance.

title: Steel Magnolias (1989)
summary: Steel Magnolias: Directed by Herbert Ross. With Sally Field, Dolly Parton, Shirley MacLaine, Daryl Hannah. A young beautician, newly arrived in a small Louisiana town, finds work at the local salon, where a small group of women share a close bond of friendship, and welcome her into the fold.

title: And God Created Woman (Et Dieu... créa la femme) (1956)
summary: Et Dieu... créa la femme: Directed by Roger Vadim. With Brigitte Bardot, Curd Jürgens, Jean-Louis Trintignant, Jane Marken. In sunny St. Tropez, a young sexpot loves one brother but marries the other.

title: Easy Money (1983)
summary: Easy Money: Directed by James Signorelli. With Rodney Dangerfield, Joe Pesci, Geraldine Fitzgerald, Candice Azzara. To inherit his mother-in-law's colossal fortune, a hard-living gambling addict must change his unhealthy ways before they get the best of him.

title: Ilsa, She Wolf of the SS (1974)
summary: Ilsa: She Wolf of the SS: Directed by Don Edmonds. With Dyanne Thorne, Gregory Knoph, Tony Mumolo, Maria Marx. Ilsa is an evil Nazi warden at a death camp that conducts "medical experiments." Ilsa's goal is to prove women can withstand more pain and suffering than men, and therefore should be allowed to fight on the front lines.

title: The Spiral Staircase (1945)
summary: De wenteltrap: Directed by Robert Siodmak. With Dorothy McGuire, George Brent, Ethel Barrymore, Kent Smith. In 1916, a shadowy serial killer is targeting women with "afflictions"; one night during a thunderstorm, the mute Helen feels menaced.
